g.text: Multi-Process VGA Demo: Concurrent Output Without Cooperation
CPU Scheduling Timeline (100 Hz timer, 50 ms slice)
Per-Process Kernel Stack (4 KB each, grows )

div.p: Each process runs in a tight busy-loop. No yield(), no sleep(), no shared flags. The 100 Hz timer IRQ preempts each process mid-loop every 50 ms without its knowledge.
Processes are unaware of each other. Hardware + scheduler enforce fairness.
